{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43591b38-42f7-4cbe-aa89-d21283c46428","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance **per HTTP request** — the framework automatically creates and disposes a scope for each request.\n\n**MAUI has no equivalent automatic scope.** There's no \"request\" concept, so the default scope is the app's root container. This means `AddScoped` behaves like `AddSingleton` — your `DbContext` lives for the entire app lifetime, accumulating tracked entities across navigations.\n\n### Fixes\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient<MyDbContext>()`** — simplest fix; gives a new instance each time it's injected.\n\n2. **Manually manage scopes** if you need shared-per-page behavior:\n   ```csharp\n   using var scope = serviceProvider.CreateScope();\n   var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n\n3. **Clear the change tracker** if you reuse the context:\n   ```csharp\n   dbContext.ChangeTracker.Clear();\n   ```\n\n`AddTransient` is usually the right answer for `DbContext` in MAUI since contexts are lightweight and short-lived by design.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"411771f6-2a2a-451d-a2ae-7f11f5dc7463","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common pitfall when migrating from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scoping — specifically why `AddScoped` behaves differently in MAUI than in ASP.NET Core.\n\nThis is a conceptual question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.\n\nThe key issue: In ASP.NET Core, a \"scope\" is created per HTTP request, so `AddScoped` gives you a new instance per request. In MAUI, there's no concept of an HTTP request scope — the default scope is the **application lifetime** itself. So `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton`, meaning your DbContext lives for the entire app lifetime, causing data to persist across navigations.","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"142F:3A3321:6EE453E:77394B9:6A03CE9E"},"id":"2337eaaf-47d3-413b-bbe4-b3bcf9ceb8b5","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:53.276Z","parentId":"d8d8a718-53b6-41ae-a16f-9fc5627bb4ba"}
